OK john  forget the DVD not needed. first is the motor out or still in  the 
bus? If still in remove from bus. If out go ahead and take the  fan( 3 bolts 
hold it in and remove the fan housing ( 4 bolts under the fan and a  couple on 
either end) do not take the fan housing apart,no need for that, nor  remove the 
alyternator. then remove the oil cooler(which needs to be  cleaned and 
resealed anyway).  I use a homemade rod( really it  is the  rod off a 36 HP motor 
that held the fan baffle on the block)  and just tap  the wrist pins out.  later 
